title: Indonesia-based agri-tech startup Semaai raises $1.25 million led by Sequoia Surge, Beenext - Economic Times
content: Indonesia-based agri-tech startup Semaai raises $1.25 million led by Sequoia Surge, Beenext  Economic Times
description: Angel investors Nipun Mehra, founder and CEO of e-commerce startup Ula; Harshet Lunani, founder and CEO of Qoala; and Prashant Pawar, technology investment banker at Houlihan Lokey, also participated in the round.
